      • authenticateEmployee

        protected final Employee authenticateEmployee(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                                              javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response)
        Checks that this request is an authorized request. Returns null if the request is unauthorized. If the request is authorized, then this method will setup the response headers so that the client has the employee information (first and last name and token). The client should always grab the token because it may change.
        Parameters:
        request - the http request being made.
        Returns:
        The employee making the request or null if the request is unauthorized.

      • processRequest

        public final void processRequest(javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                                 javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response)
                          throws java.io.IOException,
                                 javax.servlet.ServletException
        Processes the given request by doing something with the response. This method is the entry-point to this class. It is the only method that should be called by an outside entity.
        Parameters:
        request - http request being made.
        response - response to be given for this request.
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
        javax.servlet.ServletException

      • processRequest

        protected abstract void processRequest(Employee employee,
                                       javax.servlet.http.HttpServletRequest request,
                                       javax.servlet.http.HttpServletResponse response)
                                throws java.io.IOException,
                                       javax.servlet.ServletException
        This method should be implemented to add functionality to the processRequest method. Sub-classes can assume that the Employee is non-null and is an authenticated employee (or manager).
        Parameters:
        employee - Employee object used to perform data retrievals (if necessary).
        request - http request being made
        response - http response to be returned. The Employee's session token and first and last names have already been added to the headers for the response (assuming that processRequest(HttpServletRequest, HttpServletResponse) has been called prior).
        Throws:
        javax.servlet.ServletException
        java.io.IOException
        See Also:
        processRequest(HttpServletRequest, HttpServletResponse)
